The paper deals with graph visualization techniques, specifically edge bundling and coloring, which are commonly used in the field of computer graphics and visualization (cs.GR). The optimization problem and dimensionality reduction aspect of the proposed technique also suggest a potential fit for the sub-category of machine learning (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between global and local bundling, which relates to the field of distributed systems (cs.DS) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of color in visualization also suggests a potential fit for computer vision (cs.CV).
